		"description": "<p>You reach out into the spiritual realm, opening yourself up to become a temporary conduit for a wandering spirit to possess you. Roll a [[/r d6]]. On a result of 1&ndash;3, a spirit enters into your body and uses your mouth to speak. On a result of 4&ndash;6, nothing happens. The type of spirit that possesses you is determined by the Narrator.</p>\n<p>While possessed, one of your allies may ask a question of the spirit. This question must be easily answered in 25 words or less, as in the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.kbyg7uvh3w8osgiq]{Sending} spell. While the spirit is compelled to answer, it is not required to answer clearly or truthfully. When the spirit has finished, it immediately leaves you. Once you have used this ability, you may not do so again until you complete a long rest.</p>",
